{
  "stem": "9898.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And then they went to houses, and whoever had a Jew-- whoever had a beard, they cut it right off.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And this something which I never forget.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the Polish Army.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "General Haller was a famous general in the Polish Army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you know, there was-- after the First World War, the Bolsheviks attacked Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So this was during the war with the Bolsheviks, and the Bolshevik lost it because of our Marshal Pilsudski.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as I said, Aleksandrow was a small town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As far as the Jews, they were mostly not Orthodox, but, you know, I don't know how to call them, not Conservative neither, because it didn't exist such a thing.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Let's say-- my grandfather was a rabbi in a small town, a small village rather, north of Aleksandrow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had the shul, the synagogue, where my father attended.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it wasn't an Orthodox, but men were separated and the women were separated.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were upstairs sitting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I can remember it very well, because the seat was hereditary, and we were next to the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So why I mention this, because when I was a young kid-- certain things I remember, and I can still hear it-- even on Yom Kippur when the cantor was praying, singing the song 'who will live and who would die,' there was one word he screamed so loud-- [NON-ENGLISH]-- that I still hear it.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can still hear it very well.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And therefore, I told it to my rabbi, and every-- in-- in Syracuse, where we live now-- and every Yom Kippur I open the ark when the cantor prays this.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not only in Syracuse, but when I went to visit my daughter, the rabbi did the same thing there.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
